pullRequest.body:
Running
```bash
lake exe mk_all --git
```
should have the same effect as running
```bash
./script/mk_all.sh
```

that is, it creates the files `Mathlib.lean`, `Mathlib/Tactic.lean`, `Archive.lean`, `Counterexamples.lean`.

It does *not* create analogous files for `Cache` and `LongestPole`.

```bash
lake exe mk_all
```
is similar, but uses all the `.lean` files in `Mathlib`, not just the Git-managed ones.

See #11874 for using the script in CI.

nodes.body: @joneugster, do you think the same thing here as on #8361?

Not necessarily. I personally care about import-analysis tools being outside of mathlib because I want to use them in my projects without importing mathlib.

But generally, while having separate packages with useful utilities is nice for projects not depending on mathlib, with the current in-development state of lake, it's still quite tedious to keep all packages in sync and up to date...

And finally, it's quite quick to extract useful stuff out of mathlib, once somebody concretely needs it. (The only reason I see to directly PR to a separate repo is that one can save some reviewer capacity if it's only utility-code)

I also think that "import" requirements are quite project-specific.

Even this tool is not just "import all files and/or all libraries":
* `Cache` is not created;
* `Mathlib/Tactic` should also be created.

`Std` has its own tool that does something way more sophisticated.

It seems like one of these commands that are hard to implement in a way that pleases most projects.
I just reviewed the script (and some CI bits) in #11874. Summarising what I said there: looks very good, I only have minor comments.

Thanks for the quick response! I'll trust Mario and Kim on `getLeanLibs`, so this PR looks good to go, from my side.

Asking for me to learn: why are you quoting `Cli` and not `Cmd`, i.e. why does this line *not* look like this?
`def mkAll : Cmd := `[Cmd|`
That line doesn't work, this one does - if you'd like to tell me, that is welcome. It need not block this review at all.
I've copied the setup from shake. That's all I can tell ðŸ¤·
Fair enough :-)

This is completely unsubstantiated speculation: `Cli` makes me think of... well the command-line, while `Cmd` makes me think of a Lean `command`.  Maybe this is the distinction?  So, in my mind, this reads as "I'm defining a `Cmd` (in Lean), by using `Cli` syntax on the command-line".
No matter if this is true, it's certainly a useful mnemonic :-)
I believe the `Cli` here refers to the [`lean4-cli`](https://github.com/leanprover/lean4-cli) package.
:bulb: Now it makes sense! Thanks a lot!

Would it be worth to split this up into a function that returns a `List String` of the form `["Mathlib.Algebra.Algebra.Basic", "Mathlib.Algebra.Algebra.Defs", ...]`? I can imagine that form of output is more useful for other scripts.

Case in point: I need this functionality in #13245. (An array of strings is also fine for me.)

To share it, presumably this ought to go in a better place than this script (in `Mathlib/Util` perhaps? or in `Lake`).
In any case, moving this to a better place can also happen in a follow-up.

Thanks, I like this suggestions and I implemented it!

I left the function in this file, since I think that this PR already dragged quite a while...
I suppose this is okay for now. Probably we would want some sort of mechanism in Lake allowing us to differentiate build dependencies and dev dependencies.
Good point!  I added a `TODO` in the doc-module highlighting this point.
